Subject: Linux-RT 2.6.25.4-RT
From: http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/projects/rt/
Acked-by: Sven-Thorsten Dietrich <sdietrich@suse.de>
---------->

Fixes spurious system load spikes observed in /proc/loadavgrt, as described in:

  Bug 253103: /proc/loadavgrt issues weird results
  https://bugzilla.redhat.com/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=253103

Signed-off-by: Luis Claudio R. Goncalves <lgoncalv@redhat.com>>
---

---
 kernel/sched.c |    7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

Index: linux-2.6.25.4-rt1/kernel/sched.c
===================================================================
--- linux-2.6.25.4-rt1.orig/kernel/sched.c	2008-05-17 08:27:57.000000000 -0400
+++ linux-2.6.25.4-rt1/kernel/sched.c	2008-05-17 08:28:00.000000000 -0400
@@ -2428,6 +2428,13 @@ unsigned long nr_iowait(void)
 	for_each_possible_cpu(i)
 		sum += atomic_read(&cpu_rq(i)->nr_iowait);
 
+	/*
+	 * Since we read the counters lockless, it might be slightly
+	 * inaccurate. Do not allow it to go below zero though:
+	 */
+	if (unlikely((long)sum < 0))
+		sum = 0;
+
 	return sum;
 }
 
